://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L39-L40"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldOpFreeAlgebra/SuperCommute.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOpFreeAlgebra.superCommuteF\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">FieldOpFreeAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">superCommuteF</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldOpFreeAlgebra/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOpFreeAlgebra\">FieldOpFreeAlgebra</a></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldOpFreeAlgebra/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOpFreeAlgebra\">FieldOpFreeAlgebra</a></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldOpFreeAlgebra/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOpFreeAlgebra\">FieldOpFreeAlgebra</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, the super commutator `superCommuteF` is defined as the linear\nmap `𝓕.FieldOpFreeAlgebra →ₗ[ℂ] 𝓕.FieldOpFreeAlgebra →ₗ[ℂ] 𝓕.FieldOpFreeAlgebra`\nwhich on the lists `φs` and `φs'` of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp` gives\n\n`superCommuteF φs φs' = φs * φs' - 𝓢(φs, φs') • φs' * φs`.\n\nThe notation `[a, b]ₛF` can be used for `superCommuteF a b`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldOpFreeAlgebra/SuperCommute.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOpFreeAlgebra.superCommuteF","kind":"def","line":26,"name":"FieldSpecification.FieldOpFreeAlgebra.superCommuteF","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L26-L37"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldOpFreeAlgebra.Grading","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldStatistics.ExchangeSign"],"instances":[],"name":"PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldOpFreeAlgebra.SuperCommute"}